1. full form (cascading style sheet)
2. w3c (world wide web consortium)
3. selector, declaration, property, value, declaration-block
img {
  width: 300px;
}
4. Shorthand and long hand properties
5. css cpmments /* */
6. Values -
(Numeric values)
absoulte length: px,cm,mm,pt
relative length: em, rem, vw, vh
other values - keywords, functions (rotate(), calc(), url())

==== Codepen.io ==========

7. colors - (keyword, hexadecimal, rgb) (ColorZill chrome extension, https://colours.neilorangepeel.com/)
8. Selectors
type Selectors
p { color: black; }
universal Selectors
* {color: red; }
class selector
.classname { color: red; }
id selector (id and in-page linking)
#idname {color: red;}
Descendent Selectors ( DOM (Document object model))
div p a { color: red;}
.classname p {color: red;}

9. Grouping Selectors
h1, h2, .classname, #idname { color: pink;}

10. Inheritance
11. Specificity - order (universal < type (more specific, more priority) < class < id)
(Example - *, p, .class, #id, div p)

12. Cascade - Top to bottom
inside single decalration as well as on sequence of  declarations

13 !important keyword overrides source order and Specificity
p{
font-size: 12px!important
}
.example {
font-size: 16px
}
